# Performance First

Every UI should feel smooth.

Never sacrifice performance for visual effects.

## Rendering

Prefer Server Components.

Only use Client Components when interaction requires them.

## Images

Use next/image.

Lazy load when appropriate.

Avoid oversized images.

## Animations

Prefer CSS transitions.

Use transform and opacity.

Avoid animating:

- width
- height
- left
- top

Avoid layout shifts.

## Scrolling

Scrolling should remain smooth.

Avoid heavy scroll listeners.

Avoid unnecessary requestAnimationFrame loops.

No scroll hitching.

## Components

Avoid unnecessary re-renders.

Memoize only when beneficial.

Avoid deeply nested components.

## CSS

Avoid expensive selectors.

Reuse existing styles.

Avoid duplicate CSS.

## JavaScript

Avoid unnecessary effects.

Avoid unnecessary state.

Keep client-side JS minimal.

## Before Completion

Verify:

- No layout shift
- No animation jank
- No unnecessary rerenders
- Images optimized
- Lighthouse performance not negatively impacted